value.title: Zuckerberg teases agentic commerce tools and major AI rollout in 2026
value.content: Mark Zuckerberg says 2026 will be "a big year for delivering personal super intelligence."

value.title: Mark Zuckerberg says a future without smart glasses is ‘hard to imagine’
value.content: Take Zuckerberg's outlook with a grain of salt. After all, he thought we'd all be hanging out in the metaverse by now.

value.title: Tesla to invest $2B in Elon Musk’s xAI
value.content: Elon Musk's AI company xAI  disclosed earlier this month it had raised $20 billion.

value.title: Elon Musk teases a new image-labeling system for X… we think?
value.content: Elon Musk says X will begin identifying "manipulated media" but doesn't share details.

value.title: ServiceNow inks another AI partnership, this time with Anthropic
value.content: ServiceNow partners with Anthropic just a week after announcing a partnership with OpenAI as the company takes a multi-model approach.

value.title: WhatsApp will now charge AI chatbots to operate in Italy
value.content: WhatsApp plans to charge developers of AI chatbots per message.

value.title: AI data labeler Handshake buys  Cleanlab, an acquisition target of multiple others
value.content: The deal’s purpose is primarily to acquire talent, aka an acqui-hire, adding nine key Cleanlab employees to Handshake’s research organization.

value.title: Chrome takes on AI browsers with tighter Gemini integration, agentic features for autonomous tasks
value.content: Google Chrome is adding Gemini in the sidebar and is rolling out an agentic feature for AI Pro and Ultra users.

value.title: Tiny startup Arcee AI built a 400B-parameter open source LLM from scratch to best Meta’s Llama
value.content: 30-person startup Arcee AI has released a 400B model called Trinity, which it says is one of the biggest open source foundation models from a U.S. company.

value.title: With Apple’s new Creator Studio Pro, AI is a tool to aid creation, not replace it
value.content: Apple’s Creator Studio Pro leverages AI to help creators with tedious tasks — like finding clips or building slides — without trying to do the work for them.

value.title: Modelence raises $3M to smooth out the vibe-coding stack
value.content: How do you build tooling for the AI software stack? A company called Modelence has an interesting answer.

value.title: TechCrunch Disrupt 2026: Plus-one passes are almost gone and only 3 days remain
value.content: The TechCrunch Disrupt 2026 plus-one passes at 50% off are almost sold out, and this deal ends in 3 days. Register here before this deal ends on Friday, January 30 at 11:59 p.m. PT.

value.title: The AI infrastructure boom shows no sign of slowing down
value.content: ASML’s record orders show chipmakers are still betting big on AI data centers.

value.title: The conference where founders scale: TechCrunch Founder Summit 2026 tickets are now live at the lowest prices
value.content: TechCrunch Founder Summit 2026 unites 1,100 founders and investors in Boston on June 23 for a day focused on real-world scaling insights and networking that pushes the needle. Save up to $300 on your ticket.

value.title: Anthropic, Apple, OpenAI CEOs condemn ICE violence, praise Trump
value.content: Anthropic's Dario Amodei and OpenAI's Sam Altman spoke out against ICE enforcement tactics following Minneapolis violence, with one addressing concerns publicly and the other in an internal message.

value.title: Waabi raises $1B and expands into robotaxis with Uber
value.content: Waabi has secured a $750 million Series C round to accelerate autonomous trucking, and another roughly $250 million commitment from Uber to deploy 25,000 robotaxis exclusively on its platform.

value.title: Google pitches Gemini to students studying for India’s most competitive college entrance exam
value.content: Google's launch of practice tests for JEE follows its recent move to offer full-length SAT practice tests in Gemini.

value.title: Everything you need to know about viral personal AI assistant Clawdbot (now Moltbot)
value.content: Personal AI assistant Moltbot —formerly Clawdbot — has gone viral in a matter of weeks. But there’s more you should know before jumping on the bandwagon.

value.title: Anduril has invented a wild new drone-flying contest where jobs are the prize
value.content: This is a race series for software programmers and the brainchild of founder Palmer Luckey, he tells TechCrunch.

value.title: Anthropic reportedly upped its latest raise to $20B
value.content: Anthropic looks to raise $20 billion at more than $300 billion valuation, according to reports.
